          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were measured by an array of 16",
                "liquid organic scintillation detectors. The array of",
                "neutron detectors consisted of four hexagonal 5 in.",
                "thick detectors, five 7 in. x 1 in. cylindrical",
                "detectors, and seven 5 in. x 2 in. cylindrical",
                "detectors. The neutron detector array was placed 3.6",
                "m away from the center of the reaction chamber",
                "covering an angular range from 11deg to 39deg."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Low energy silicon-strip detector array",
                "LESA consisted of four identical 300 mu-m thick",
                "silicon-pad detectors, each of which has four strips",
                "and a total area of 4 x 4 cm2. The silicon detector",
                "array was placed inside the reaction chamber,",
                "covering an angular range from 90deg to 150deg."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF",
                "PSD",
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron energy was determined by time",
                "of flight after pulse shape analysis was performed to",
                "select neutrons. Coincidence between neutron",
                "detectors and LESA array was required. Excited unbound",
                "states of 18Ne were produced via reaction",
                "16-O(3He,n)18Ne. Properties of 18Ne unbound states were",
                "studied using coincidences of neutrons populating",
                "unbound states of 18Ne and charged particles emitted",
                "in decays of these states."
              ]
            }
          ],
